title: Apollo 11 Launch
description: Apollo 11, the first lunar landing mission, is launched from Kennedy Space Center.

title: Apollo 11 Enters Lunar Orbit
description: Apollo 11 fires its engine to become captured by the Moon's gravity and enters lunar orbit.

title: Lunar Module Separation
description: The Lunar Module, named 'Eagle', separates from the Command Module for its descent to the lunar surface.

title: Lunar Module Touchdown
description: 'Eagle' lands in the Sea of Tranquility. Neil Armstrong reports: 'The Eagle has landed.'

title: First Man on the Moon
description: Neil Armstrong becomes the first person to step onto the lunar surface.

title: Second Man on the Moon
description: Buzz Aldrin becomes the second person to step onto the lunar surface.

title: Lunar Module Liftoff
description: The Lunar Module ascends from the lunar surface to rendezvous and dock with the Command Module.

title: Return to Earth
description: The spacecraft fires its engine to leave lunar orbit and return to Earth.

title: Splashdown in Pacific Ocean
description: Apollo 11 splashes down in the Pacific Ocean, approximately 812 nautical miles southwest of Hawaii.

title: Recovery of Astronauts
description: Astronauts are recovered by the USS Hornet recovery ship.

title: Quarantine Begins
description: Astronauts begin quarantine that lasts until August 10, 1969.
